1
00:00:21,035 --> 00:00:22,435
You don't need to make amends.

2
00:00:23,435 --> 00:00:24,435
You're excused.

3
00:00:25,605 --> 00:00:26,675
This is a chance.

4
00:00:29,135 --> 00:00:30,905
So today I'm going to...

5
00:00:33,775 --> 00:00:37,375
do something for my country.

6
00:01:14,675 --> 00:01:15,975
(Episode 12)

7
00:01:17,205 --> 00:01:21,005
Do you know what happens when a ghost pretends to be a human?

8
00:01:22,705 --> 00:01:23,935
Su Hyeon.

9
00:01:24,235 --> 00:01:26,005
As the obsession grows,

10
00:01:26,575 --> 00:01:28,675
you'll feel sorry about yourself...

11
00:01:29,305 --> 00:01:31,905
and you'll bear a grudge.

12
00:01:33,705 --> 00:01:34,835
Ryu Su Hyeon.

13
00:01:35,775 --> 00:01:39,175
If you have a conscience, let go of your greed.

14
00:01:39,935 --> 00:01:43,535
If you don't want to be wandering as an evil spirit, just leave.

15
00:01:46,735 --> 00:01:47,775
Su Hyeon.

16
00:01:49,735 --> 00:01:51,105
Hey, Su Hyeon.

17
00:01:59,105 --> 00:02:01,375
(Chicago Typewriter)

18
00:02:23,145 --> 00:02:24,575
You are still here.

19
00:02:25,675 --> 00:02:27,105
No, it's not that.

20
00:02:27,905 --> 00:02:29,645
I just came, sir.

21
00:02:34,735 --> 00:02:36,145
Ms. Kang.

22
00:02:38,805 --> 00:02:41,475
Right. I forgot that I came home.

23
00:02:43,935 --> 00:02:45,105
I am sorry.

24
00:02:45,475 --> 00:02:48,175
You kept smiling strangely while sleeping.

25
00:02:48,435 --> 00:02:51,175
And I wondered if you were suffering from the side effect of concussion.

26
00:02:51,175 --> 00:02:54,305
Strangely. Did you say I was smiling strangely?

27
00:02:56,535 --> 00:02:57,605
Sir.

28
00:02:58,505 --> 00:03:02,375
I know you just got involved in a relationship,

29
00:03:02,675 --> 00:03:04,635
but can I be frank with you?

30
00:03:04,735 --> 00:03:06,775
I'm not in a relationship.

31
00:03:08,975 --> 00:03:10,905
Go ahead.

32
00:03:10,975 --> 00:03:13,435
If your behavior is unsophisticated like that,

33
00:03:13,505 --> 00:03:15,935
you can't win a girl's heart.

34
00:03:17,075 --> 00:03:18,475
Unsophisticated?

35
00:03:22,735 --> 00:03:25,905
But I'm a writer with emotions that are complex, sensitive,

36
00:03:26,705 --> 00:03:30,105
and delicate. Are you sure you're referring to me?

37
00:03:30,235 --> 00:03:31,905
- Yes. You. - Yes. You.

38
00:03:32,135 --> 00:03:35,475
What are you talking about? I'm worried because I have a poker face.

39
00:03:36,175 --> 00:03:37,375
- A poker face? - A poker face?

40
00:03:37,635 --> 00:03:39,405
Do you mean a see-through face?

41
00:03:39,405 --> 00:03:40,875
All your emotions show up on your face.

42
00:03:40,875 --> 00:03:44,175
When you don't like someone, you act like a vengeful warrior.

43
00:03:44,175 --> 00:03:46,905
Like a fighter who is willing to sacrifice her life for her faith.

44
00:03:46,905 --> 00:03:48,505
Like a fighter who aims for your vital points.

45
00:03:48,505 --> 00:03:51,675
You become unbelievably blunt when you don't like someone.

46
00:03:52,005 --> 00:03:53,175
But when you are in front of someone you like...

47
00:03:55,035 --> 00:03:56,275
Mr. Han?

48
00:03:57,835 --> 00:04:00,005
You become like that.

49
00:04:00,005 --> 00:04:01,205
Am I your toy?

50
00:04:01,205 --> 00:04:02,635
Mr. Han!

51
00:04:05,435 --> 00:04:07,735
Your face turns like that.

52
00:04:07,935 --> 00:04:10,205
She's almost like Pavlov's dog.

53
00:04:10,905 --> 00:04:12,335
Pavlov's dog?

54
00:04:12,475 --> 00:04:14,875
Ivan Pavlov was a Russian physiologist,

55
00:04:15,005 --> 00:04:16,905
who did a research on classical conditioning...

56
00:04:16,975 --> 00:04:20,705
by checking how much a dog salivates while getting fed.

57
00:04:21,135 --> 00:04:23,505
- Ms. Kang. - And during the experiment,

58
00:04:23,535 --> 00:04:26,035
he accidentally found out that the dog salivated even when...

59
00:04:26,035 --> 00:04:29,205
he hears the footsteps of the person feeding him...

60
00:04:29,205 --> 00:04:31,475
or when he saw his feeding bowl.

61
00:04:31,605 --> 00:04:34,635
Therefore, that dog learned to associate the footsteps...

62
00:04:34,635 --> 00:04:37,535
and the bowl with his food.

63
00:04:37,575 --> 00:04:39,375
And he started to respond unconditionally.

64
00:04:41,605 --> 00:04:44,235
Right. Did you feed Gyun Woo?

65
00:04:44,705 --> 00:04:48,535
Should we do a little test?

66
00:04:48,905 --> 00:04:52,945
First, I will bring in the person who will help us with the test.

67
00:04:53,945 --> 00:04:55,635
Please come in, Seol.

68
00:04:58,975 --> 00:05:00,005
Mr. Han?

69
00:05:02,505 --> 00:05:03,835
Did you see that?

70
00:05:04,075 --> 00:05:05,675
Just like Pavlov's dog that salivated...

71
00:05:05,675 --> 00:05:07,635
as he heard the footsteps and saw his bowl,

72
00:05:07,635 --> 00:05:11,675
you react unconditionally to Seol's name alone.

73
00:05:13,035 --> 00:05:15,105
- Ms. Kang. - Mr. Han.

74
00:05:15,705 --> 00:05:17,005
You should admit it now.

75
00:05:17,205 --> 00:05:18,735
You are very simple.

76
00:05:19,035 --> 00:05:21,875
When it comes to dating, you are a two-dimensional person...

77
00:05:22,135 --> 00:05:24,275
in the three-dimensional world.

78
00:05:24,945 --> 00:05:27,375
You only have the front and the back sides.

79
00:05:27,735 --> 00:05:30,805
You are two-dimensional and as simple as a paper doll.

80
00:05:32,575 --> 00:05:33,975
Am I not charming because of that?

81
00:05:34,075 --> 00:05:37,005
Not charming at all. Girls are more touched by...

82
00:05:37,005 --> 00:05:38,935
the clumsy words spoken by the man she likes...

83
00:05:39,175 --> 00:05:43,805
than the perfect love confession told by the man she doesn't like.

84
00:05:45,735 --> 00:05:47,735
There's not much tension between us.

85
00:05:47,805 --> 00:05:50,375
There's none.

86
00:05:50,675 --> 00:05:53,235
As soon as a man catches a fish and puts it in his fish tank,

87
00:05:53,275 --> 00:05:55,475
he gets ready to catch another fish.

88
00:05:55,635 --> 00:05:59,335
Unfortunately, that's the hunting instinct of men...

89
00:05:59,535 --> 00:06:00,905
we were born with.

90
00:06:03,405 --> 00:06:04,435
Dae Han,

91
00:06:04,835 --> 00:06:07,235
I think I know why you can't date.

92
00:06:08,335 --> 00:06:12,205
What do you mean I've never dated anyone?

93
00:06:12,575 --> 00:06:15,605
You learned love through theories in books.

94
00:06:16,275 --> 00:06:18,735
Thank you for your sincere words,

95
00:06:19,375 --> 00:06:22,605
but I will follow my own way.

96
00:06:23,605 --> 00:06:26,735
What is your way?

97
00:06:27,175 --> 00:06:29,635
There's no U-turn in my love. There's only going straight.

98
00:06:29,635 --> 00:06:31,005
I won't play any games.

99
00:06:32,635 --> 00:06:33,735
I will just move forward.

100
00:06:35,235 --> 00:06:37,035
- I'm leaving. - Why?

101
00:06:37,535 --> 00:06:39,405
Food is coming out soon. Aren't you going to eat it?

102
00:06:39,405 --> 00:06:40,905
I need sleep more than food.

103
00:06:41,505 --> 00:06:44,175
I stayed up a few nights at the clinic, and I'm tired.

104
00:06:44,605 --> 00:06:47,935
Did you stay all night with Se Ju?

105
00:06:51,905 --> 00:06:53,675
Bang Jin, you should take your time.

106
00:06:54,805 --> 00:06:56,335
Dae Han, I'm sorry about what I said earlier.

107
00:06:56,535 --> 00:06:59,575
You are a good man, so someone great will show up.

108
00:06:59,605 --> 00:07:00,675
Bye.

109
00:07:01,305 --> 00:07:02,705
That's not a blessing, is it?

110
00:07:02,975 --> 00:07:05,305
She just rejected me. She just pierced a knife through my heart.

111
00:07:08,475 --> 00:07:11,205
I heard you are hiring a part-timer.

112
00:07:11,205 --> 00:07:13,335
Wait. Dae Han.

113
00:07:16,205 --> 00:07:18,835
I'm sorry, but we found one about two days ago.

114
00:07:18,835 --> 00:07:19,875
Really?

115
00:07:20,235 --> 00:07:22,035
- Yes. - Is there anything I can do?

116
00:07:22,305 --> 00:07:25,875
I quit my other job because I wanted to learn Italian cuisine.

117
00:07:25,875 --> 00:07:27,805
But we don't have any plans to hire more staff.

118
00:07:27,805 --> 00:07:30,175
I will clean, serve, and do the dishes as well.

119
00:07:30,575 --> 00:07:33,575
Just let me learn whenever I find time. Please?

120
00:07:34,235 --> 00:07:36,505
Goodness. What do I do?

121
00:07:36,735 --> 00:07:38,805
You should hire her, Boss.

122
00:07:39,175 --> 00:07:41,375
I heard you're lacking hands these days.

123
00:07:41,505 --> 00:07:42,535
Should I?

124
00:07:42,735 --> 00:07:44,335
If you say so.

125
00:07:46,205 --> 00:07:48,305
He's just like Pavlov's Dog too.

126
00:07:50,275 --> 00:07:51,275
Excuse me.

127
00:07:51,905 --> 00:07:55,005
Thank you. I got this part-time job thanks to you.

128
00:07:55,005 --> 00:07:57,805
No problem. Your boss is a great man,

129
00:07:57,805 --> 00:07:59,675
so please do your best to help him out. Bye.

130
00:08:13,605 --> 00:08:15,305
We're supposed to meet. Why are you calling me instead?

131
00:08:15,705 --> 00:08:17,475
Don't tell me you changed your mind already.

132
00:08:19,105 --> 00:08:20,405
You want to change our meeting place?

133
00:08:35,435 --> 00:08:36,435
Sit down.

134
00:08:45,075 --> 00:08:46,775
You're braver than I thought.

135
00:08:47,335 --> 00:08:49,545
You had the guts to call me to your workroom.

136
00:08:50,075 --> 00:08:52,275
I couldn't find a better place to talk in private.

137
00:08:52,275 --> 00:08:53,805
You can talk to me more comfortably.

138
00:08:53,975 --> 00:08:56,975
It's not like I'll stop threatening you even if you act so nicely.

139
00:08:57,375 --> 00:08:58,805
You're only making me feel uncomfortable.

140
00:09:00,135 --> 00:09:01,775
What do you want from me?

141
00:09:02,205 --> 00:09:03,705
You're not that smart, are you?

142
00:09:04,175 --> 00:09:07,575
What would I want from threatening you? It's obviously money.

143
00:09:08,805 --> 00:09:12,105
Would you like to give me cash, or would you prefer wiring the money?

144
00:09:14,435 --> 00:09:15,635
Before that,

145
00:09:16,705 --> 00:09:17,805
you should take a look at this.

146
00:09:34,635 --> 00:09:36,675
You've prepared a strong card.

147
00:09:37,575 --> 00:09:39,045
Did you order someone to tail me?

148
00:09:39,175 --> 00:09:40,175
Don't worry.

149
00:09:40,775 --> 00:09:42,605
As long as you don't say anything,

150
00:09:42,935 --> 00:09:45,175
I won't be talking either.

151
00:09:46,235 --> 00:09:47,305
What do you think?

152
00:09:47,775 --> 00:09:49,205
Does our deal satisfy you?

153
00:09:51,275 --> 00:09:52,775
Not really.

154
00:09:53,045 --> 00:09:55,705
But I'll admit that you're quite difficult to deal with.

155
00:09:59,435 --> 00:10:03,175
I hope you live a great life, Mr. Baek Tae Min.

156
00:10:04,405 --> 00:10:06,075
Shall I give you an advice?

157
00:10:07,545 --> 00:10:10,975
Your target, Han Se Ju, is not an easy fellow.

158
00:10:12,575 --> 00:10:15,505
He's probably on the move to catch you right now.

159
00:10:22,675 --> 00:10:25,505
Why do you think my target is Han Se Ju?

160
00:10:27,575 --> 00:10:28,575
Then who is it?

161
00:10:30,435 --> 00:10:31,675
I don't know.

162
00:10:33,335 --> 00:10:35,075
If it's not Han Se Ju,

163
00:10:36,405 --> 00:10:37,735
who do you think it could be?

164
00:10:42,805 --> 00:10:45,045
My goodness, it feels so refreshing to drink this after a nice bath.

165
00:10:46,305 --> 00:10:48,705
Taking a bath after a long nap...

166
00:10:48,705 --> 00:10:50,175
makes me feel so refreshed.

167
00:10:50,305 --> 00:10:52,305
It was so hard to scrub off my mom's dead skin cells.

168
00:10:52,305 --> 00:10:53,975
I almost broke my wrist.

169
00:10:54,105 --> 00:10:55,375
You're like an eraser.

170
00:10:55,435 --> 00:10:57,535
The dead skin cells just kept on coming out.

171
00:10:57,535 --> 00:10:59,235
They weren't dead skin cells. You just scrubbed off my skin.

172
00:10:59,235 --> 00:11:02,505
You won't believe how much strength this brat put in while scrubbing me.

173
00:11:02,505 --> 00:11:05,135
Look here. It's so red.

174
00:11:05,135 --> 00:11:07,035
- My goodness, it stings. - She's not kidding.

175
00:11:07,035 --> 00:11:09,735
You became so strong after eating so many dishes of seolleongtang.

176
00:11:09,735 --> 00:11:12,105
My gosh, Mr. Han.

177
00:11:12,175 --> 00:11:14,105
Hey, you can't fool me anymore.

178
00:11:14,435 --> 00:11:15,475
I'm not kidding.

179
00:11:15,805 --> 00:11:16,805
Gosh.

180
00:11:19,405 --> 00:11:22,435
He's here again. Why does he keep coming here?

181
00:11:22,505 --> 00:11:24,205
Don't push me, you brat.

182
00:11:34,275 --> 00:11:35,735
Are you on your way home from the bathhouse?

183
00:11:37,675 --> 00:11:40,335
He shouldn't ask a lady that kind of question.

184
00:11:40,335 --> 00:11:42,735
Mr. Han is quite an amateur.

185
00:11:45,335 --> 00:11:46,505
No.

186
00:11:46,875 --> 00:11:49,005
My goodness, did she just lie?

187
00:11:49,275 --> 00:11:51,805
He'll probably know she's lying because she has no makeup on.

188
00:11:54,405 --> 00:11:57,205
You didn't run away yet.

189
00:11:58,575 --> 00:11:59,805
Did you try flipping a coin?

190
00:12:02,075 --> 00:12:04,235
Why? You said you were going to flip it again.

191
00:12:06,405 --> 00:12:08,105
I decided to follow my heart...

192
00:12:09,405 --> 00:12:12,105
rather than follow the decisions of the coins.

193
00:12:14,075 --> 00:12:15,805
You made a very nice decision.

194
00:12:20,705 --> 00:12:22,535
But why can't you look at me?

195
00:12:25,475 --> 00:12:26,705
You must have no makeup on.

196
00:12:27,305 --> 00:12:30,475
- My goodness, don't say that. - My goodness, don't say that.

197
00:12:33,405 --> 00:12:36,605
If you have more to say, I'll be right back.

198
00:12:39,805 --> 00:12:41,035
Did you really quit...

199
00:12:42,035 --> 00:12:43,805
working as Tae Min's assistant?

200
00:12:44,175 --> 00:12:48,335
Gosh, I need to go inside and at least apply some BB cream.

201
00:12:49,005 --> 00:12:51,805
Why are you asking me that again?

202
00:12:52,175 --> 00:12:54,575
Because I don't want you to be around him.

203
00:12:55,535 --> 00:12:57,175
I want you to quit.

204
00:13:00,505 --> 00:13:04,205
Can't you also do this for me?

205
00:13:10,075 --> 00:13:11,205
Okay, fine.

206
00:13:13,335 --> 00:13:16,535
I'll be right back after I...

207
00:13:16,535 --> 00:13:17,575
Would you...

208
00:13:18,735 --> 00:13:20,875
like to write the novel with me?

209
00:13:22,235 --> 00:13:23,235
What?

210
00:13:23,235 --> 00:13:24,875
You could be scared because you're uncertain.

211
00:13:25,605 --> 00:13:27,435
Once you find out, it might not be a big deal.

212
00:13:28,305 --> 00:13:31,505
We could put together both of our memories.

213
00:13:31,805 --> 00:13:35,035
Let's see what's in that box together.

214
00:13:37,235 --> 00:13:38,805
Let's write it together.

215
00:13:39,905 --> 00:13:40,975
All three of us.

216
00:13:42,375 --> 00:13:43,375
"Three"?

217
00:13:43,635 --> 00:13:45,805
I told you about the mysterious being.

218
00:13:47,575 --> 00:13:50,335
The guy who waited almost 100 years...

219
00:13:50,735 --> 00:13:52,805
so that he could meet us.

220
00:13:55,105 --> 00:13:56,175
And...

221
00:13:57,975 --> 00:13:59,075
And?

222
00:14:00,535 --> 00:14:03,305
You still look pretty without any makeup.

223
00:14:11,675 --> 00:14:13,105
What? They caught the suspect?

224
00:14:13,205 --> 00:14:15,335
Yes. The police just called.

225
00:14:15,405 --> 00:14:17,475
I'm going to go straight to the police station.

226
00:14:17,475 --> 00:14:19,075
Call Se Ju and tell him to meet me there.

227
00:14:19,075 --> 00:14:20,235
Call his lawyer too.

228
00:14:20,375 --> 00:14:21,705
While he was running away,

229
00:14:21,705 --> 00:14:25,005
there was a car parked nearby. The black box must've caught him.

230
00:14:25,005 --> 00:14:29,005
They checked the footage and found his license plate number.

231
00:14:29,005 --> 00:14:31,205
The owner of the car called him to handle it with insurance.

232
00:14:31,205 --> 00:14:33,335
That's when he must've thought, "My gosh, I got caught."

233
00:14:33,335 --> 00:14:36,705
"I guess I'll have to turn myself in." That's what happened.

234
00:14:36,705 --> 00:14:37,875
What does he do?

235
00:14:37,875 --> 00:14:40,405
He has no job. He's one of those cyberbullies.

236
00:14:40,405 --> 00:14:43,435
He probably just goes to an internet cafe to write bad stuff about you.

237
00:14:43,435 --> 00:14:46,005
A cyberbully tried to attempt terror?

238
00:14:46,935 --> 00:14:48,305
That doesn't happen often.

239
00:14:48,305 --> 00:14:50,375
Are you trying to write a novel? Why are you looking for a probability?

240
00:14:50,375 --> 00:14:52,105
He turned himself in.

241
00:14:52,235 --> 00:14:53,875
The reason why he tried to harm you is more absurd.

242
00:14:54,005 --> 00:14:55,075
I'm sorry.

243
00:14:57,205 --> 00:14:58,635
I couldn't find a job,

244
00:14:59,075 --> 00:15:01,105
and my family treats me like a nobody.

245
00:15:01,605 --> 00:15:05,035
But Mr. Han lives with a crown on his head.

246
00:15:05,175 --> 00:15:06,735
He lives a totally different life.

247
00:15:06,735 --> 00:15:08,105
He goes on dates with pretty girls.

248
00:15:08,105 --> 00:15:10,305
I suddenly got so angry at him.

249
00:15:10,305 --> 00:15:11,505
You little...

250
00:15:12,135 --> 00:15:13,775
So that's why you tried to hit him with your motorcycle?

251
00:15:13,775 --> 00:15:16,035
Don't you know that the crown carries great responsibilities?

252
00:15:16,035 --> 00:15:18,875
You dare to claim the crown when you have no sense of responsibility?

253
00:15:18,875 --> 00:15:19,905
You want that crown on your head?

254
00:15:19,905 --> 00:15:22,275
What are you doing? Calm down.

255
00:15:22,975 --> 00:15:24,275
My goodness.

256
00:15:26,435 --> 00:15:29,005
I'm really sorry. I'll never do it again.

257
00:15:30,275 --> 00:15:34,675
Mr. Han. I promise I'll never write bad stuff about you on the internet.

258
00:15:34,735 --> 00:15:38,305
Please forgive me just this once. Please, Mr. Han.

259
00:15:39,735 --> 00:15:40,775
My gosh.

260
00:15:40,775 --> 00:15:43,705
Hey, Se Ju. How can you just let him go like that?

261
00:15:43,705 --> 00:15:45,435
He almost killed you.

262
00:15:46,175 --> 00:15:47,435
He said he's sorry.

263
00:15:47,435 --> 00:15:49,675
He said he regrets what he did. Why bother taking it further?

264
00:15:49,805 --> 00:15:52,735
Who would actually be confident in that kind of situation?

265
00:15:52,735 --> 00:15:54,505
He only did that because he didn't want to go to prison.

266
00:15:55,235 --> 00:15:56,975
He probably wants to believe that he's sorry.

267
00:15:58,005 --> 00:16:01,775
Please call the media and deal with them.

268
00:16:02,105 --> 00:16:05,135
Please prevent that crazy jerk's identity from getting revealed.

269
00:16:05,135 --> 00:16:07,675
What are you talking about? Do you think he's actually sorry?

270
00:16:07,675 --> 00:16:10,175
Those kinds of guys are really diligent in their own ways.

271
00:16:10,175 --> 00:16:12,175
I bet he'll change his user name and do something worse.

272
00:16:12,235 --> 00:16:13,435
He's young.

273
00:16:13,705 --> 00:16:15,775
I just don't want to ruin his future.

274
00:16:16,275 --> 00:16:17,805
Anyway, I'll trust you with this.

275
00:16:21,035 --> 00:16:23,275
I don't understand why people think he's difficult.

276
00:16:23,275 --> 00:16:24,775
He's like a foolish donkey.

277
00:16:26,475 --> 00:16:28,435
But I wonder if it'll be okay to just let him go.

278
00:16:29,905 --> 00:16:31,575
This doesn't feel right.

279
00:16:31,935 --> 00:16:33,135
I got released.

280
00:16:34,105 --> 00:16:37,075
You were right. I begged on my knees...

281
00:16:37,705 --> 00:16:39,775
and cried my eyes out.

282
00:16:39,775 --> 00:16:40,805
So he just let me go.

283
00:16:44,205 --> 00:16:45,975
What? 500 dollars?

284
00:16:49,275 --> 00:16:50,705
My goodness.

285
00:16:53,235 --> 00:16:55,075
You little brat.

286
00:16:55,475 --> 00:16:58,475
I almost went to prison because of you.

287
00:16:59,035 --> 00:17:00,235
But you're only going to give me 500 dollars?

288
00:17:00,305 --> 00:17:01,875
You didn't go to prison after all.

289
00:17:03,035 --> 00:17:04,875
I'll give you 600 dollars. That's it.

290
00:17:06,875 --> 00:17:09,875
Otherwise, I'm going to tell the police that you steal motorcycles.

291
00:17:10,805 --> 00:17:12,675
I have enough evidence,

292
00:17:12,675 --> 00:17:14,575
so don't even try to threaten me.

293
00:17:22,105 --> 00:17:23,205
Hello.

294
00:17:23,275 --> 00:17:25,675
Hey. I guess you started working here.

295
00:17:25,805 --> 00:17:27,405
- Is it fun? - Yes.

296
00:17:27,475 --> 00:17:29,705
I have so much to learn. It's really fun.

297
00:17:30,805 --> 00:17:34,635
Is that lunch box for your boyfriend?

298
00:17:34,635 --> 00:17:38,905
Well, yes. How did you know?

299
00:17:38,905 --> 00:17:40,475
I saw my boss...

300
00:17:40,475 --> 00:17:42,405
crying his eyes out while making that.

301
00:17:43,435 --> 00:17:44,875
It must taste salty, then.

302
00:17:45,075 --> 00:17:48,175
I'm not sure who your boyfriend is, but he must be so happy.

303
00:17:48,375 --> 00:17:50,975
He has such a sweet and pretty girlfriend like you.

304
00:17:51,175 --> 00:17:52,975
Gosh, I'm flattered.

305
00:17:52,975 --> 00:17:54,175
Sapsari.

306
00:17:58,405 --> 00:18:00,335
How did you know I'd be here?

307
00:18:00,575 --> 00:18:03,005
I went to your place to pick you up and was told you'd be here.

308
00:18:07,245 --> 00:18:09,275
Oh, I should get back inside.

309
00:18:09,405 --> 00:18:10,435
Okay.

310
00:18:17,675 --> 00:18:18,745
What is it?

311
00:18:20,875 --> 00:18:23,135
I was just thinking that she looks familiar for some reason.

312
00:18:23,435 --> 00:18:25,375
Familiar, my foot.

313
00:18:25,635 --> 00:18:27,535
It must be because she's young and pretty.

314
00:18:27,535 --> 00:18:28,905
Men are all the same.

315
00:18:29,135 --> 00:18:30,905
Jealousy isn't good for your body.

316
00:18:30,905 --> 00:18:31,935
I'm not jealous.

317
00:18:32,075 --> 00:18:33,405
I like seeing you jealous though.

318
00:18:35,335 --> 00:18:36,805
He's good with words.

319
00:18:39,475 --> 00:18:42,675
"When the roses bloom and your heart flutters,"

320
00:18:43,075 --> 00:18:45,275
"give me that smile of yours."

321
00:18:46,405 --> 00:18:48,405
"If there's a song you have to sing,"

322
00:18:48,905 --> 00:18:50,375
"sing it now."

323
00:18:51,705 --> 00:18:53,675
"When your sun goes down,"

324
00:18:54,335 --> 00:18:56,535
"it'll be too late for you to sing it."

325
00:18:57,635 --> 00:18:59,135
"Sing your song..."

326
00:19:00,175 --> 00:19:01,675
"right at this moment."

327
00:19:03,805 --> 00:19:05,575
Shall we go back to Chicago?

328
00:19:18,605 --> 00:19:21,705
Shall we just go back and settle down?

329
00:19:22,535 --> 00:19:24,475
Until we're summoned by those in the upper world.

330
00:19:35,405 --> 00:19:37,035
Shall I go back in there...

331
00:19:39,975 --> 00:19:41,605
and never come out again?

332
00:19:48,675 --> 00:19:50,335
(Send me back...)

333
00:19:52,875 --> 00:19:53,875
(to Chicago.)

334
00:19:56,635 --> 00:19:57,675
Come in.

335
00:19:58,245 --> 00:20:00,475
Hey you, old man. Where are you?

336
00:20:01,075 --> 00:20:03,035
Come out. We have a guest.

337
00:20:15,805 --> 00:20:17,035
Has he come out?

338
00:20:17,245 --> 00:20:18,575
Is he here now?

339
00:20:19,775 --> 00:20:20,805
Yes.

340
00:20:21,635 --> 00:20:24,905
He's standing before you right now looking completely dumbfounded.

341
00:20:34,075 --> 00:20:36,005
Hello, it's nice to see... Right,

342
00:20:36,535 --> 00:20:37,705
I can't see him.

343
00:20:41,335 --> 00:20:42,935
It's nice to meet you.

344
00:20:43,875 --> 00:20:45,405
I'm Jeon Seol.

345
00:20:45,675 --> 00:20:48,475
I was Ryu Su Hyeon in my past life.

346
00:20:53,135 --> 00:20:57,575
Mr. Han told me all about you.

347
00:21:03,035 --> 00:21:05,575
Welcome to this life.

348
00:21:13,075 --> 00:21:14,775
He looks like he's about to burst into tears.

349
00:21:22,875 --> 00:21:24,005
But...

350
00:21:24,575 --> 00:21:26,205
is he really here now?

351
00:21:27,675 --> 00:21:29,305
You better not be fooling me.

352
00:21:29,705 --> 00:21:31,335
Here we go again.

353
00:21:32,405 --> 00:21:34,305
Gosh, how can I prove this?

354
00:21:38,435 --> 00:21:39,675
Use a coin.

355
00:21:41,405 --> 00:21:43,405
Tell her to flip a coin.

356
00:21:43,535 --> 00:21:44,635
Why should she flip a coin...

357
00:21:47,975 --> 00:21:49,275
Like in "Ghost"?

358
00:21:51,735 --> 00:21:55,335
You must carry coins like the bible since your religion worships them.

359
00:21:55,335 --> 00:21:56,335
Take one out.

360
00:22:05,135 --> 00:22:06,875
The side with the image means he's here,

361
00:22:06,875 --> 00:22:08,775
and the side with the number means he's not.

362
00:22:08,775 --> 00:22:09,775
Okay?

363
00:22:10,535 --> 00:22:11,535
Now, toss it.

364
00:22:51,275 --> 00:22:52,335
What?

365
00:22:52,675 --> 00:22:55,235
Tell her to open her hand.

366
00:22:55,805 --> 00:22:57,975
You're such a nuisance. All right.

367
00:22:59,005 --> 00:23:01,035
He's saying you should open your hand.

368
00:23:19,775 --> 00:23:23,175
Yul is really here with us now.

369
00:23:39,805 --> 00:23:41,805
If the two of you are done with greeting each other,

370
00:23:42,075 --> 00:23:46,135
let's go to the writing room and work on planning the novel.

371
00:23:46,505 --> 00:23:48,335
No, wait.

372
00:23:48,775 --> 00:23:49,875
Give me a minute.

373
00:23:50,135 --> 00:23:52,535
No, just 30 seconds. Come in after 30 seconds.

374
00:23:55,275 --> 00:23:56,435
What's the matter with him?

375
00:23:57,175 --> 00:23:59,275
Why? What did he say?

376
00:24:04,975 --> 00:24:06,275
Why did he lock the door?

377
00:24:07,035 --> 00:24:08,035
(Send me back to Chicago.)

378
00:24:10,875 --> 00:24:13,575
Hey, that's my writing room.

379
00:24:18,975 --> 00:24:20,075
My goodness.

380
00:24:20,175 --> 00:24:21,705
The door opened on its own.

381
00:24:22,375 --> 00:24:23,575
That's nothing.

382
00:24:24,305 --> 00:24:27,475
Just think that you're at one of those haunted houses at theme parks,

383
00:24:27,675 --> 00:24:28,975
and enjoy it.

384
00:24:29,375 --> 00:24:30,435
Come in.

385
00:24:46,175 --> 00:24:47,805
I thought he would've been reincarnated like us,

386
00:24:48,975 --> 00:24:51,305
living his life somewhere in the world now.

387
00:24:53,475 --> 00:24:55,505
What on earth happened to him...

388
00:24:55,575 --> 00:24:59,335
for him to have been locked up in that thing for 80 years?

389
00:25:01,975 --> 00:25:04,335
That's what we're trying to find out now.

390
00:25:05,275 --> 00:25:07,535
And that's why we want to complete the novel.

391
00:25:08,875 --> 00:25:11,005
When our memories come together,

392
00:25:11,805 --> 00:25:13,475
the puzzle might become complete.

393
00:25:15,635 --> 00:25:17,005
I'll do my best.

394
00:25:17,805 --> 00:25:18,805
Good.

395
00:25:19,775 --> 00:25:22,005
Then shall we write up a contract?

396
00:25:22,775 --> 00:25:23,805
Again?

397
00:25:24,075 --> 00:25:25,075
Write what?

398
00:25:26,805 --> 00:25:29,075
A contract for co-authoring the novel.

399
00:25:32,175 --> 00:25:33,705
The typewriter is typing on its own.

400
00:25:36,805 --> 00:25:38,975
Co-authoring terms and conditions.

401
00:25:39,075 --> 00:25:40,975
Clause One. "I, Han Se Ju..."

402
00:25:40,975 --> 00:25:42,235
"I, Yoo Jin Oh..."

403
00:25:42,235 --> 00:25:43,235
"I, Jeon Seol..."

404
00:25:43,235 --> 00:25:46,435
"We will share our memories with each other..."

405
00:25:46,605 --> 00:25:49,175
- "until we complete the novel." - Good. "Han Se Ju will..."

406
00:25:49,175 --> 00:25:51,805
"The process will be based on trust."

407
00:25:51,805 --> 00:25:54,475
"Hence, we must not keep any secrets from each other,"

408
00:25:54,535 --> 00:25:56,375
"and we must not betray each other."

409
00:25:56,605 --> 00:25:58,035
My turn. "Han Se Ju will..."

410
00:25:58,035 --> 00:25:59,235
A special clause for Jeon Seol.

411
00:25:59,905 --> 00:26:02,275
"Even after the novel is completed,"

412
00:26:03,535 --> 00:26:07,175
"she will do her best in her relationship with Han Se Ju."

413
00:26:09,675 --> 00:26:10,675
Done.

414
00:26:11,575 --> 00:26:12,675
- Done? - Done?

415
00:26:12,805 --> 00:26:15,675
All right. We can sign it later.

416
00:26:15,875 --> 00:26:19,305
Let's have a glass of champagne to celebrate coming together like this.

417
00:26:23,175 --> 00:26:24,305
Well, I...

418
00:26:24,475 --> 00:26:26,375
I didn't get to include any clauses that I want.

419
00:26:26,375 --> 00:26:28,235
- Me neither. - Cut it out.

420
00:26:28,235 --> 00:26:29,735
Everything we need is already in it.

421
00:26:29,735 --> 00:26:33,435
Only those who are childish and small-minded write long contracts.

422
00:26:34,705 --> 00:26:37,005
- Let's go. - That is true, but it's still...

423
00:26:37,575 --> 00:26:38,635
Goodness.

424
00:26:46,735 --> 00:26:48,705
I honestly can't get used to it.

425
00:26:50,005 --> 00:26:53,735
Now, you must be able to understand how wrongly accused I've been.

426
00:26:54,705 --> 00:26:55,805
Of what?

427
00:26:56,105 --> 00:26:58,535
Oh, when I thought you're the one who ripped my purse?

428
00:26:59,775 --> 00:27:00,805
That's not everything.

429
00:27:00,905 --> 00:27:04,175
He's the one who made that earthquake break out here.

430
00:27:04,175 --> 00:27:07,605
He's also the one who's been secretly opening doors for you.

431
00:27:08,075 --> 00:27:09,205
Well...

432
00:27:09,375 --> 00:27:13,305
It's safe to assume that most of the misunderstandings...

433
00:27:13,675 --> 00:27:15,635
you've had about me were caused by this guy.

434
00:27:16,405 --> 00:27:17,535
You're at it again!

435
00:27:18,175 --> 00:27:20,775
Why do you never tell people about the time I saved your life?

436
00:27:20,975 --> 00:27:24,135
What about the fun times the two of you had thanks to me?

437
00:27:25,775 --> 00:27:28,035
He's saying something to you now, isn't he?

438
00:27:28,475 --> 00:27:29,605
What did he say?

439
00:27:30,475 --> 00:27:31,575
Nothing important.

440
00:27:31,975 --> 00:27:35,175
He just said that he feels very bad for trying to get between us...

441
00:27:35,435 --> 00:27:37,035
and doing sleazy things.

442
00:27:37,675 --> 00:27:39,005
Gosh, when did I...

443
00:27:42,975 --> 00:27:45,505
Goodness. He passed away.

444
00:27:46,135 --> 00:27:48,675
- Did someone pass away? - A senior writer.

445
00:27:49,135 --> 00:27:50,675
Writer Moon Seol Woo. You know him, right?

446
00:27:51,075 --> 00:27:53,805
- He had been ill. - Shouldn't you go to his funeral?

447
00:27:54,135 --> 00:27:55,675
I should get going too.

448
00:27:57,475 --> 00:28:00,075
No. Just stay with him.

449
00:28:00,135 --> 00:28:03,175
The hospital is near here, so I'll just drop by and say hi.

450
00:28:03,535 --> 00:28:05,135
I didn't know him in person.

451
00:28:05,675 --> 00:28:07,305
Then you should take your time.

452
00:28:07,505 --> 00:28:09,135
I will play with Gyun Woo.

453
00:28:09,805 --> 00:28:12,075
- No. - Goodness.

454
00:28:12,475 --> 00:28:14,575
You are scarier than the ghost.

455
00:28:14,705 --> 00:28:16,075
Why can't I?

456
00:28:17,605 --> 00:28:21,235
Gyun Woo is losing his hair because he's too tired.

457
00:28:22,605 --> 00:28:24,175
Don't touch him.

458
00:28:27,335 --> 00:28:28,505
You.

459
00:28:29,375 --> 00:28:31,105
You remember that you're not supposed to possess someone...

460
00:28:31,135 --> 00:28:34,805
without my consent, right?

461
00:28:34,805 --> 00:28:37,435
- That was just with you. - I'm going to call an exorcist.

462
00:28:41,375 --> 00:28:44,005
Why are you whispering for such a long time?

463
00:28:44,575 --> 00:28:45,705
Are you two seeing each other?

464
00:28:47,135 --> 00:28:50,005
This is what it means to talk nonsense.

465
00:28:51,875 --> 00:28:53,135
I will be right back.

466
00:29:15,235 --> 00:29:17,335
Is it okay to leave them by themselves?

467
00:29:19,975 --> 00:29:21,675
She can't even see him anyway.

468
00:29:24,335 --> 00:29:26,905
It feels like we're on a blind date.

469
00:29:29,475 --> 00:29:31,205
You are there, right?

470
00:29:34,405 --> 00:29:36,105
I can't hear you even if you answer me.

471
00:29:41,405 --> 00:29:42,505
Why don't we do this?

472
00:29:43,435 --> 00:29:44,805
I will ask you a question.

473
00:29:45,275 --> 00:29:48,135
Try to tap the champagne glass with your hand.

474
00:29:48,735 --> 00:29:51,475
Then perhaps the drink will ripple.

475
00:29:52,375 --> 00:29:54,575
If the answer is yes, make it ripple. If it's no, make it still.

476
00:29:55,405 --> 00:29:56,475
Shall we try it?

477
00:29:59,975 --> 00:30:03,775
Are you there right now?

478
00:30:16,105 --> 00:30:17,175
It works.

479
00:30:18,675 --> 00:30:20,175
Then I will ask a proper question.

480
00:30:20,935 --> 00:30:25,075
Did you come to a cart bar one time to see me?

481
00:30:32,605 --> 00:30:33,975
I knew it.

482
00:30:35,475 --> 00:30:37,575
There was nobody else there,

483
00:30:38,175 --> 00:30:41,905
but I felt like someone was watching me.

484
00:30:42,475 --> 00:30:43,705
It was just like right now.

485
00:30:56,505 --> 00:30:58,975
Were you there when my shoelaces were untied?

486
00:31:07,975 --> 00:31:11,635
It was you. You were the man Mr. Han mentioned.

487
00:31:18,535 --> 00:31:20,405
I want to see your face.

488
00:31:27,635 --> 00:31:30,605
Actually, I know your face, Jin Oh.

489
00:31:31,375 --> 00:31:32,775
I saw you in my dream.

490
00:31:38,075 --> 00:31:41,175
Your form is unstable. Don't be afraid to recoil from it.

491
00:31:41,235 --> 00:31:44,435
When that happens, your body moves back or your arm sags.

492
00:31:45,175 --> 00:31:46,875
Then you lose stability and control.

493
00:31:49,735 --> 00:31:50,775
Aim.

494
00:31:56,305 --> 00:31:57,335
Shoot.

495
00:31:58,405 --> 00:32:02,235
You were really handsome. You were just like a prince.

496
00:32:07,375 --> 00:32:09,375
You were my shooting instructor, weren't you?

497
00:32:11,105 --> 00:32:12,275
Thank you.

498
00:32:12,735 --> 00:32:14,605
Thanks to you,

499
00:32:14,935 --> 00:32:18,035
I became a national shooter for a while.

500
00:32:21,505 --> 00:32:22,605
Good job.

501
00:32:22,905 --> 00:32:24,735
It's all thanks to you.

502
00:32:26,875 --> 00:32:27,905
Don't forget.

503
00:32:28,275 --> 00:32:30,435
Don't move back because you're afraid of recoiling from it.

504
00:32:33,075 --> 00:32:34,775
Don't take your eyes off of the target.

505
00:32:35,675 --> 00:32:37,005
It's just like being in love, isn't it?

506
00:32:40,805 --> 00:32:43,705
We have the same memories, but we long them differently.

507
00:32:44,275 --> 00:32:47,535
I should see you in person and thank you.

508
00:32:49,105 --> 00:32:51,135
Please forgive your unworthy pupil.

509
00:32:52,805 --> 00:32:56,275
Before I met you, I read a poem like this.

510
00:32:57,235 --> 00:32:58,305
Do you want to hear it?

511
00:32:59,105 --> 00:33:01,335
I can understand why Bang Jin can see you.

512
00:33:02,105 --> 00:33:04,175
But Mr. Han sees you too.

513
00:33:04,305 --> 00:33:07,805
How come I can't see you?

514
00:33:08,205 --> 00:33:11,805
"When the roses bloom and your heart flutters,"

515
00:33:13,075 --> 00:33:15,575
"give me that smile of yours."

516
00:33:18,235 --> 00:33:20,435
There must be a way.

517
00:33:21,035 --> 00:33:25,235
"If there's a song you have to sing, sing it now."

518
00:33:31,135 --> 00:33:32,535
I knew this would happen.

519
00:33:33,975 --> 00:33:36,635
Something came up, and Mr. Han can't come early.

520
00:33:37,105 --> 00:33:40,635
It's too bad, but we should end it here.

521
00:33:41,375 --> 00:33:43,335
"When your sun goes down,"

522
00:33:44,305 --> 00:33:46,535
"it'll be too late for you to sing it."

523
00:33:47,605 --> 00:33:49,235
I'll get going now.

524
00:33:49,905 --> 00:33:51,375
"Sing your song..."

525
00:33:54,105 --> 00:33:55,235
Bye.

526
00:33:55,675 --> 00:33:57,175
"right at this moment."

527
00:33:58,075 --> 00:34:00,675
I will see you again.

528
00:34:02,635 --> 00:34:04,175
"Sing your song..."

529
00:34:05,305 --> 00:34:06,435
"right at this moment."

