00:52:38,252 --> 00:52:40,022
Is that why you've kept it only from me?

806
00:52:42,652 --> 00:52:43,722
No.

807
00:52:47,382 --> 00:52:49,022
Because I was afraid that I might hesitate.

808
00:52:54,052 --> 00:52:55,052
Seol.

809
00:52:57,652 --> 00:52:59,122
What's going on? Why are you still here?

810
00:53:07,252 --> 00:53:08,322
What's wrong?

811
00:53:10,482 --> 00:53:12,722
Did you remember something again?

812
00:53:16,852 --> 00:53:18,452
Are you crying or smiling?

813
00:53:19,052 --> 00:53:20,752
Are you sad or happy?

814
00:53:22,552 --> 00:53:24,022
It wasn't you.

815
00:53:24,582 --> 00:53:27,722
- What do you mean? - You're not the person I killed.

816
00:53:28,422 --> 00:53:30,822
- What? - I had remembered it wrong.

817
00:53:31,252 --> 00:53:32,722
It wasn't a sad scene.

818
00:53:33,152 --> 00:53:34,722
It was an emotional yet romantic scene...

819
00:53:34,782 --> 00:53:36,422
where a couple couldn't be honest to each other.

820
00:53:41,482 --> 00:53:42,982
Jin Oh, you were right.

821
00:53:43,252 --> 00:53:44,452
I was mistaken.

822
00:53:45,182 --> 00:53:47,752
I'm glad to hear that a happy memory came back to you.

823
00:53:50,322 --> 00:53:51,352
What was that about?

824
00:53:52,552 --> 00:53:53,622
By any chance...

825
00:53:55,782 --> 00:53:56,882
Were you two...

826
00:53:57,352 --> 00:53:59,452
just talking to each other?

827
00:54:01,322 --> 00:54:03,022
Shall we have a party to celebrate it?

828
00:54:04,382 --> 00:54:05,622
Shall we really do that?

829
00:54:08,152 --> 00:54:09,822
Wait, hold on a second.

830
00:54:09,822 --> 00:54:11,752
Are you saying he has become...

831
00:54:12,982 --> 00:54:14,052
visible to you?

832
00:54:15,322 --> 00:54:16,352
- Yes. - Yes.

833
00:54:21,722 --> 00:54:23,382
Why are you suddenly being like this?

834
00:54:24,222 --> 00:54:25,252
When did it start?

835
00:54:26,752 --> 00:54:27,782
What do you mean?

836
00:54:27,782 --> 00:54:30,222
When did you become visible to her?

837
00:54:31,322 --> 00:54:34,252
That's... It started today, but...

838
00:54:34,452 --> 00:54:35,652
When did you find out?

839
00:54:35,782 --> 00:54:38,182
- Find out what? - Don't make me repeat myself.

840
00:54:39,122 --> 00:54:40,952
How you can become visible to people.

841
00:54:41,152 --> 00:54:42,522
When did you find out?

842
00:54:44,052 --> 00:54:46,382
Can we complete the novel first?

843
00:54:49,182 --> 00:54:51,552
You're one shameless ghost.

844
00:54:51,922 --> 00:54:53,582
You almost jeopardized our friendship.

845
00:54:53,582 --> 00:54:55,582
- How can you try to get out... - Did you...

846
00:54:56,782 --> 00:54:58,452
just say "friendship"?

847
00:55:00,422 --> 00:55:02,122
Friendship.

848
00:55:02,652 --> 00:55:03,782
Did you really say that?

849
00:55:06,522 --> 00:55:09,282
Well, I think I said something similar.

850
00:55:11,082 --> 00:55:12,222
Don't worry.

851
00:55:12,752 --> 00:55:13,752
I promise you...

852
00:55:14,622 --> 00:55:16,322
that I will never do anything...

853
00:55:17,082 --> 00:55:18,752
that could jeopardize our friendship.

854
00:55:32,182 --> 00:55:35,352
Do you hear our friendship breaking up?

855
00:55:36,352 --> 00:55:37,652
Don't you worry.

856
00:55:38,352 --> 00:55:39,382
As you know,

857
00:55:40,052 --> 00:55:42,122
I'll disappear eventually because I'm a ghost.

858
00:55:49,882 --> 00:55:51,652
Did I sound sad?

859
00:55:52,482 --> 00:55:57,322
I just wanted to tell you we don't have much time left together.

860
00:55:57,882 --> 00:55:59,052
- Let's write. - Let's write.

861
00:56:00,252 --> 00:56:01,352
Shall we?

862
00:56:17,482 --> 00:56:18,822
- What should we write first? - What should we write first?

863
00:56:28,352 --> 00:56:30,652
I should use this.

864
00:56:31,982 --> 00:56:33,452
(Carpe Diem)

865
00:56:34,152 --> 00:56:36,952
Are you asking us to smoke?

866
00:56:37,922 --> 00:56:40,482
No, I'm going to send you two...

867
00:56:40,652 --> 00:56:44,282
to Kyungsung in 1930 with this match.

868
00:56:46,222 --> 00:56:47,252
Pardon?

869
00:56:48,652 --> 00:56:50,222
Was it you then?

870
00:56:53,882 --> 00:56:55,382
Step aside.

871
00:56:56,182 --> 00:56:57,482
Step aside.

872
00:57:09,152 --> 00:57:11,552
Is it some kind of time travel?

873
00:57:11,552 --> 00:57:14,952
Kind of. But technically, it's experiencing your past life.

874
00:57:15,222 --> 00:57:18,652
It might not look awesome, but I'm using the rest of my energy for it.

875
00:57:19,052 --> 00:57:20,982
I wish you two have a good time there...

876
00:57:21,122 --> 00:57:22,852
and hope it helps you write.

877
00:57:23,322 --> 00:57:26,922
Why do you keep saying "you two"?

878
00:57:28,082 --> 00:57:29,152
Aren't you coming with us?

879
00:57:29,152 --> 00:57:31,352
I can't come with you, not that I don't want to.

880
00:57:31,722 --> 00:57:35,422
Only humans can do this. As a ghost, I can't.

881
00:57:35,852 --> 00:57:38,282
Would you like to try?

882
00:57:40,782 --> 00:57:41,922
No, I'm not going.

883
00:57:42,582 --> 00:57:44,282
I had enough of confusion.

884
00:57:44,622 --> 00:57:45,722
I'm out of this.

885
00:57:46,422 --> 00:57:47,652
I'm definitely going.

886
00:57:48,882 --> 00:57:51,952
If you're not coming, I'll go alone.

887
00:57:51,952 --> 00:57:53,152
You can't go alone.

888
00:57:53,452 --> 00:57:55,282
What if something happens to you?

889
00:57:57,252 --> 00:57:58,322
Fine.

890
00:58:03,322 --> 00:58:05,552
Are you ready?

891
00:58:13,622 --> 00:58:15,952
Then let's go.

892
00:58:37,622 --> 00:58:38,722
Run!

893
00:58:39,482 --> 00:58:40,982
- Hurry up! - Run!

894
00:58:43,222 --> 00:58:44,522
What are you doing? Run!

895
00:58:45,452 --> 00:58:47,522
- Stop! - Stop there!

896
00:59:17,452 --> 00:59:19,422
It has worn out over the years.

897
01:00:46,982 --> 01:00:49,982
(Chicago Typewriter)

898
01:00:49,982 --> 01:00:53,222
How about we write together?

899
01:00:53,352 --> 01:00:55,722
The three of us. Hello, it's nice to meet you.

900
01:00:55,722 --> 01:00:57,782
Su Hyeon. Ryu Su Hyeon.

901
01:00:58,452 --> 01:00:59,652
I can see you.

902
01:00:59,652 --> 01:01:03,582
I will send you to Kyungsung in 1930 with this match.

903
01:01:04,622 --> 01:01:06,622
- Run! - What are you doing? Run!

904
01:01:07,622 --> 01:01:11,122
What is this? Why are Hui Young's things...

905
01:01:17,122 --> 01:01:18,782
That's me.

906
01:01:19,882 --> 01:01:21,222
Who is he waiting for?

907
01:01:21,582 --> 01:01:22,852
I'm sorry I have kept you waiting.
